cookingMethod.S:
1) First, make the dressing by adding the oil, lemon juice & zest, garlic powder, and salt & pepper to a small bowl and mixing well.

2) Next, add your cooked pasta to a large bowl and then add the shredded carrot, sweetcorn, diced pepper, and drained tuna. Pour the dressing over the top and then use a large spoon to carefully mix everything together so it’s all evenly distributed.

3) Portion up into 3 meal prep containers and store in the fridge for the next few days. Lunch sorted.

1. Place 3/4 cup of yogurt in a bowl.

2.Wash and slice your berries, place on top of the yogurt.

3. Drizzle honey over top.

4. Enjoy as an amazing breakfast!

For those who count calories, the honey is 60 cals, blueberries are 42 cals and the strawberries are 49 cals for a grand total of  271 protein packed, antioxidant loaded, delicious calories.

I totally have a new favorite breakfast.

1)Melt butter in a stockpot over medium heat. Add onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened. Stir in broccoli. Add broth and simmer until broccoli is tender, 10 to 15 minutes.

2)Reduce heat; add cheese cubes and stir until melted. Stir in milk and garlic powder.

3)Stir cornstarch and water together in a small bowl until smooth. Stir into soup; cook, stirring frequently, until thick.

STEP 1
Heat oven to 190C/170C fan/gas 5. Spread the almonds on a baking tray and roast for 10 mins. Remove and allow to cool.

STEP 2
Put into a food processor and whizz for 12 mins, stopping every so often to scrape the sides down, and finish with a drizzle of honey. Serve spread over malt loaf or wholegrain bread. Will keep in the fridge for up to 3 weeks.

Cut the sweet potatoes into wedges.
Sprinkle the flour, salt, pepper and
melted coconut oil over them about a
little to coat them (this will make them
super-crispy). Pop them onto a baking
tray and bake at 200°C for 25 minutes.
Coat each steak with pink peppercorns
(crushed) and sea salt, then fry or
griddle on high heat with the coconut
oil. When the pan just about begins to
smoke, add the tuna steaks and fry on
each side for 45 seconds if you prefer
seared tuna, or 2 minutes on each side
if you prefer it cooked through.
Serve with lemon wedges and your
favourite vegetables.

title.S: Seared tuna steak & sweet potato wedges

cookingMethod.S:
1)First, in a bowl add the mango pulp and Clear Whey.  

2)Blitz with a handheld blender until it’s completely smooth.  

3)Grab a pan and add milk and a sachet of gelatine, and wait a few minutes for the gelatine to “bloom” (ie do its thing).  

4)Put on the hob over a low temperature and mix until the gelatine is completely dissolved.  

5)Add the protein powder and mango pulp mix to the pan and stir well.  

6)Then line six silicone cupcake moulds onto a tray and pour in the mix.  

7)Allow to set in the fridge for four hours.

1. Preheat oven to 200°C or 180°C for fan-assisted. In a large bowl, whisk together cashew butter, soy sauce, maple syrup, garlic and five spice.

2. Add the diced chicken and broccoli florets to the bowl and coat well.

3. Pour the contents of the bowl into a deep baking tray and bake for 20 minutes.

4. Meanwhile, toast your cashew nuts. Heat a frying pan on a high heat, add the cashews and don’t move them until they begin to brown and pop a little. Toss and allow to brown on the other side.

5. Once the cashew chicken and broccoli are baked, stir through the cashew nuts and chillies, divide and place into Tupperware boxes with the cooked basmati rice. Sprinkle a little chopped coriander over each and refrigerate. Easy!

Cut chicken breasts into cubes, season, and pan fry on a medium heat with a little coconut oil until fully cooked through. Remove and allow to cool. Cook the rice. Rinse under cold water, and then cook for either 1 minute in the microwave or 2-3 minutes in a pan. Set aside and allow to cool a little. Assemble your mason jars. Divide and drop in the chopped tomatoes and onions, lime juice and a little salt and pepper and mix. Add 2 tbsp. soured cream to each jar. By adding the liquid first, you won’t get a soggy salad after a few days in the fridge. Divide the sweetcorn amongst the jars, then add the rice, chicken, avocado, little gem lettuce leaves and the cheese. Screw on the lid and enjoy 4 days’ worth of healthy lunches!

1)With a spoon, press down on the center of the bread to form a pocket.
2)Line the edges of the bread with butter, and crack an egg into the pocket.
3)Line the edges of the bread with shredded cheese.
4)Sprinkle on salt and pepper, and bake at 400°F (204°C) for 10-15 min. 10 min will have a runny yolk whereas 15 min will have a firmer yolk.

Add all ingredients to a blender and
blend on full power.

Mix all of the ingredients together and
drop into a jar.
Refrigerate for at least two hours
or overnight.

STEP 1

Combine all salad dressing ingredients in small bowl; mix well. Set aside.

STEP 2

Melt butter in 10-inch skillet until sizzling; add broken ramen noodles and almonds. Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, 2-3 minutes or until almonds and noodles are lightly toasted. Drain on paper towels.

STEP 3

Just before serving, combine dressing, toasted noodles and almonds, cabbage(sliced) and green onions in large bowl; toss until well coated.
